com.gmail.socraticphoenix.asmsig.builder

Class MethodSignatureBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • MethodSignatureBuilder

  • public class MethodSignatureBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    A utility class to build a method signature. It attempts to parse a signature first, and if that fails it will build a signature with no generic information from the method's descriptor. To successfully build a method signature, every method in this class must be called. The submitDesc(String) must be called, followed by all the remaining methods in any order.

    • Method Detail

      • submitSignature

        public MethodSignatureBuilder submitSignature(java.lang.String signature)
        Submits a method signature for parsing by this signature builder. The signature may be null, and if it is, the builder will use the information provided by the other methods to construct the signature.
        Parameters:
        signature - The method signature.
        Returns:
        This, for method chaining.

      • submitDesc

        public MethodSignatureBuilder submitDesc(java.lang.String desc)
        Submits the method descriptor to this signature builder. If the signature was previously submitted and was nonnull, this method will be ignored. Otherwise, the given descriptor will be used to build the method signature.
        Parameters:
        desc - The method descriptor.
        Returns:
        This, for method chaining.

      • submitExceptions

        public MethodSignatureBuilder submitExceptions(java.lang.String... exceptions)
        Submits the names of the exceptions associated with the method to this signature builder. If the signature was previously submitted and was nonnull, this method will be ignored. Otherwise, the given exceptions will be used to build the method signature.
        Parameters:
        exceptions - The exceptions associated with the method.
        Returns:
        This, for method chaining.
